<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idcfc889cd-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0" identifier="/us/usc/t48/s2169"><num value="2169">§ 2169.</num><heading> Abstention</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this subchapter prevents a district court in the interests of justice from abstaining from hearing a particular proceeding arising in or related to a case under this subchapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idcfc889ce-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0">(<ref href="/us/pl/114/187/tIII/s309">Pub. L. 114–187, title III, § 309</ref>, <date date="2016-06-30">June 30, 2016</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/130/583">130 Stat. 583</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
